  "title": "Exceptional Fee Product Feature",
  "description": "A Product Feature that specifies a temporary, conditional, or customer-specific fee applied in addition to or instead of the standard product fees. Exceptional fees capture special charges that are outside the normal product pricing rules, reflecting specific agreements, regulatory requirements, or situational conditions.\r\n\r\nExamples\r\n\r\n- Campus Support Fee: A temporary $10 processing fee for transactions at a specific university location.\r\n\r\n- Premium Service Charge: A negotiated fee applied for expedited loan processing for corporate clients.\r\n\r\n- Regulatory Surcharge: Temporary compliance-related fee for a specific transaction type.",
